  <span id="freeText3206593218209624682" style="display:none">Rick H. Veal knocks it out of the park with Lexi's Legacy Book 2 of <br />The Master of Whitehall...Best Paranormal Book I've read since Anne Rice's "Vampire Chronicles"...and the love story continues...Lexi tells her story while the author keeps everyone in the know on how the story began in The Master of Whitehall...What should Katelyn do when she finds out her best friend has terminal cancer? She decides to let her choose between death and a "gift" of eternal life. When Lexi chooses the "gift" it begins a reaction to show that maybe living life after having been so close to death opens your eyes to new ways to live. Once she chooses to live, Lexi does just that..she lives..she becomes more passionate about life and embraces everything around her. Beautifully written Lexi's Legacy will keep you on the edge of your seat just waiting to see what adventure in life she will take you on next...Brilliant!!!</span>
