        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1169654641" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6355456532419135536">This is the 2nd book of The Master of Whitehall series and continues from where the first book left off. However you can read this as a stand alone book. This is the continuation of Lexi&apos;s (Alexis Corbin) story. After Lexi had found out she was dying, her friend Katelyn explained to Lexi that she was a vampire (that took a little convincing) and that she could give Lexi The Gift, to become an immortal and vampire. Katelyn explained to her all that it entailed and it was left to Lexi to accept or</span>
  <span id="freeText6355456532419135536" style="display:none">This is the 2nd book of The Master of Whitehall series and continues from where the first book left off. However you can read this as a stand alone book. This is the continuation of Lexi's (Alexis Corbin) story. After Lexi had found out she was dying, her friend Katelyn explained to Lexi that she was a vampire (that took a little convincing) and that she could give Lexi The Gift, to become an immortal and vampire. Katelyn explained to her all that it entailed and it was left to Lexi to accept or not. Lexi wanted to live so therefore she accepted The Gift. Lexi went through the transition exceptionally well. She is now enjoying her immortal life except for one thing. All of her new family (Katelyn &amp; James; Charlotte Ann &amp; Dale) have mates and she would love to have one herself to share her immortal life with. She does meet someone she thinks will make a wonderful mate, but tragically that relationship doesn't work out. She meets Gale (Charlotte Ann asked her to keep an eye on Lexi) who happens to be an Ancient and who is Charlotte Ann's sire. Gale doesn't have a mate at this time and she helps Lexi get over the tragic love affair. They become friends and Gale asks Lexi to go with her on a sort-of grand tour. Lexi agrees feeling it would be good to get away or a while. Her family agrees even though Katelyn is sad to see her go but feels it's the best thing for Lexi now.<br /><br />This is not your usual gory vampire story, there is some bloodletting but not much at all. I just love the interaction with all the characters and how their lives intertwine with each other. A novel idea how they all become such a loving family and how they will do anything for each other, even help with revenge if asked. I find the way the author writes about the history of vampirism is fascinating. I just love this series and I'm sure the next one will be just as good.<br />*This book was a gift from the author for an honest review*<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6355456532419135536" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


