<span id="freeTextContainer10206749752306940717">3 Stars<br/><br/>This book picks up where Lexi became a vampire. It is mostly told from her point of view, although at the beginning it is from Katelyn&apos;s point. Their is way to much detail, making the story sound monotonous and long-winded. <br/><br/>The author spent so much time on the detail, he failed to grow and further develop his characters. I struggled to read this story due to the amount of excessive detail. <br/><br/><br/>On the plus side, you actually get to learn more about Lexi and a little more about Dale and Charlot</span>
  <span id="freeText10206749752306940717" style="display:none">3 Stars<br /><br />This book picks up where Lexi became a vampire. It is mostly told from her point of view, although at the beginning it is from Katelyn's point. Their is way to much detail, making the story sound monotonous and long-winded. <br /><br />The author spent so much time on the detail, he failed to grow and further develop his characters. I struggled to read this story due to the amount of excessive detail. <br /><br /><br />On the plus side, you actually get to learn more about Lexi and a little more about Dale and Charlotte Ann as well.<br /></span>
