<div id="review_1401438057" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1401438057" />
    <a title="Renee Kennedy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/46779646-renee-kennedy"><img alt="Renee Kennedy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442180065p2/46779646.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1401438057?book_show_action=true">Sep 26, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Renee Kennedy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Renee Kennedy" href="/user/show/46779646-renee-kennedy">Renee Kennedy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" " href="/book/show/23297897-lexi-s-legacy---the-saga-continues">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1401438057" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1710899740613409443">Rick Veal knows how to write vampire stories that aren&apos;t cliche or corny. This book drew me in and I&apos;m not a fan of the paranormal genre. It was written in such a beautiful way, the characters are rich and emotionally deep. <br/>I&apos;ve never been to Charleston, SC but through Lexi&apos;s Legacy, I can see it in vivid details. I really enjoyed this book, it is book two in the series but I do believe you can read it as a standalone. </span>
  <span id="freeText1710899740613409443" style="display:none">Rick Veal knows how to write vampire stories that aren't cliche or corny. This book drew me in and I'm not a fan of the paranormal genre. It was written in such a beautiful way, the characters are rich and emotionally deep. <br />I've never been to Charleston, SC but through Lexi's Legacy, I can see it in vivid details. I really enjoyed this book, it is book two in the series but I do believe you can read it as a standalone. </span>
